## AhaDiff

Use AhaDiff as the learn-back layer for AI-written diffs:

- `ahadiff learn HEAD~1..HEAD` after a commit.
- `ahadiff learn --staged` before committing staged changes.
- `ahadiff quiz <run_id>` and `ahadiff review` for retention.
- `ahadiff verify <run_id>` when checking an existing run.
- `ahadiff improve <run_id>` for a targeted follow-up.
- `ahadiff serve` to inspect local run artifacts.

Keep explanations grounded in verified claims and file-line evidence. Treat
`.ahadiff/review.sqlite`, `.ahadiff/runs/`, and `prompts/` as local state unless
the repository explicitly documents otherwise.

For Aider, consider starting with `--read CONVENTIONS.md` when this repository
uses that convention. A project `.aider.conf.yml` can also include optional
read-only context files, but provider secrets should stay in environment
variables, not repository files.
